A man who escaped in the Motetema Policing area outside Groblersdal, Limpopo has been rearrested.Tonko Gift Tshehla, 20, was re-arrested on Monday at his hideout in Sephaku Village in Hlogotlou policing area following a tip-off from members of the community.Tshehla is due to appear before the Motetema Magistrate&#8217;s Court on a charge of escaping from lawful custody and on his original multiple charges of rape.Tshehla was originally arrested for a case of rape which he committed during 2016 and he was later linked to another five (5) cases of rape which he committed during 2014.Police investigations are continuing.-TNA Reporter 